{"content":"---\ntitle: \"<faultPropagationQuery>\"\nms.date: \"03/30/2017\"\nms.topic: \"reference\"\nms.assetid: 4fb5c2b1-3dad-4eca-9c7f-3efb51899813\n---\n\n# \\<faultPropagationQuery>\n\nRepresents a query that is used to track the handling of faults that occur within an activity.  This event occurs each time a FaultHandler processes a fault. You should use such query to track the handling of faults that occur within an activity. The query is necessary for a  tracking participant to subscribe to fault propagation records.\n\n For more information on tracking profile queries, see [Tracking Profiles](../../../../../docs/framework/windows-workflow-foundation/tracking-profiles.md).\n\n\\<system.serviceModel>\\\n\\<tracking>\\\n\\<trackingProfile>\\\n\\<workflow>\\\n\\<faultPropagationQueries>\\\n\\<faultPropagationQuery>\n\n## Syntax\n\n```xml\n<tracking>\n  <trackingProfile name=\"Name\">\n    <workflow>\n      <faultPropagationQueries>\n        <faultPropagationQuery activityName=\"String\"\n                               faultHandlerActivityName=\"String\" />\n      </faultPropagationQueries>\n    </workflow>\n  </trackingProfile>\n</tracking>\n```\n\n## Attributes and Elements\n\nThe following sections describe attributes, child elements, and parent elements.\n\n### Attributes\n\n|Attribute|Description|\n|---------------|-----------------|\n|activityName|A string that specifies the name of the fault handler activity that propagated the fault. The default is *, which indicates that fault propagation records are returned for all activities.|\n|faultHandlerActivityName|A string that specifies the name of the activity that was the source of the fault.|\n\n### Child Elements\n\nNone.\n\n### Parent Elements\n\n|Element|Description|\n|-------------|-----------------|\n|[\\<faultPropagationQueries>](../../../../../docs/framework/configure-apps/file-schema/windows-workflow-foundation/faultpropagationqueries.md)|Represents a list of configuration elements that are used to track the handling of faults that occur within an activity.  This event occurs each time a FaultHandler processes a fault.|\n\n## See also\n\n- <xref:System.ServiceModel.Activities.Tracking.Configuration.FaultPropagationQueryElement?displayProperty=nameWithType>\n- <xref:System.Activities.Tracking.FaultPropagationQuery?displayProperty=nameWithType>\n- [Workflow Tracking and Tracing](../../../../../docs/framework/windows-workflow-foundation/workflow-tracking-and-tracing.md)\n- [Tracking Profiles](../../../../../docs/framework/windows-workflow-foundation/tracking-profiles.md)\n","nodes":[{"pos":[4,129],"embed":true,"restype":"x-metadata","content":"title: \"<faultPropagationQuery>\"\nms.date: \"03/30/2017\"\nms.topic: \"reference\"\nms.assetid: 4fb5c2b1-3dad-4eca-9c7f-3efb51899813","nodes":[{"content":"<faultPropagationQuery>","nodes":[],"path":["title"],"nosxs":false}],"yml":true},{"pos":[137,161],"content":"\\<faultPropagationQuery>","linkify":"\\<faultPropagationQuery>","nodes":[{"content":"<ph id=\"ph1\">\\&lt;</ph>faultPropagationQuery&gt;","pos":[0,24],"source":"\\<faultPropagationQuery>"}]},{"content":"Represents a query that is used to track the handling of faults that occur within an activity.","pos":[163,257]},{"content":"This event occurs each time a FaultHandler processes a fault.","pos":[259,320]},{"content":"You should use such query to track the handling of faults that occur within an activity.","pos":[321,409]},{"content":"The query is necessary for a  tracking participant to subscribe to fault propagation records.","pos":[410,503]},{"pos":[506,660],"content":"For more information on tracking profile queries, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Tracking Profiles<ept id=\"p1\">](../../../../../docs/framework/windows-workflow-foundation/tracking-profiles.md)</ept>.","source":"For more information on tracking profile queries, see [Tracking Profiles](../../../../../docs/framework/windows-workflow-foundation/tracking-profiles.md)."},{"content":"<ph id=\"ph1\">\\&lt;